Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • Graph

  • public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
    This graph provides a representation of the airports, their delays and the length of the flights between airports. Airports are represented using nodes while flights are represented using edges.
    Author:
    Claudia Tu z3459448

    • Method Detail

      • addNode

        public void addNode(java.lang.String name,
           int delay)
        Adds a node to the graph. The node represents an airport. The name parameter represents the name of the airport, for example "Sydney". The delay parameter is the delay experienced in minutes at the airport before a plane can leave for another airport.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the node as a string.
        delay - The delay experienced at the node as an int.

      • getNode

        public Node getNode(java.lang.String name)
        Returns the node (or airport) with the given name.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the node as a string.
        Returns:
        The corresponding node.

      • getNodes

        Returns:
        The nodes from this graph as a HashSet.

      • addEdge

        public void addEdge(java.lang.String from,
           java.lang.String to,
           java.lang.Integer weight)
        Adds an edge to the graph. The edge represents a flight between two given airports. The weight of the edge is the length of the flight in minutes.
        Parameters:
        from - The name of the node that the edge starts from as a string.
        to - The name of the node that the edge ends at as a string.
        weight - The weight of the edge as an int.

      • getEdge

        public Edge getEdge(java.lang.String from,
           java.lang.String to)
        Returns the edge between the two nodes which are identified using their names, or the flight between two airports.
        Parameters:
        from - The name of the node at which the edge begins as a string.
        to - The name of the node at which the edge ends as a string.
        Returns:
        The edge between the nodes corresponding to the given names.
